  <p id="Xwo84W">Elon Musk says X’s — formerly Twitter’s — block feature is on the chopping block, repeating his long-standing gripe against the basic social networking feature. “Block is going to be deleted as a ‘feature’, except for DMs,” Musk <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1692558414105186796?t=EdyRxGsju67txX8rd9bEIg&amp;s=19">said in an X reply</a> on Friday. He followed up with <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1692558493255942213">another post</a>: “It makes no sense.”</p>
<p id="Fl8YcB">Musk has made his feelings about blocking known in the past months. In June, he said that <a href="https://www.techdirt.com/2023/06/09/elon-musk-says-twitter-is-going-to-get-rid-of-the-block-feature-enabling-greater-harassment/">Twitter should remove blocking</a> in favor of “a stronger form of mute,” and he’s complained about <a href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1624678792550846464?lang=en">large block lists</a> and <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/elon-musk-weighs-campaign-block-195927685.html?guccounter=1">mass blocking campaigns</a> against users who subscribe to Twitter Blue. But he also has a long history of promises that are delayed or never implemented — and removing the “block” feature might be a particularly unpopular...</p>
